Error: Throwable <i> Error </i> exceptions are typically unrecoverable external errors and are unchecked.These exceptions are automatically 
thrown to the calling method if created..
RuntimeException: A throwable RuntimeException is typically caused by programming mistakes , and is unchecked . It is automatically 
thrown to the calling method.
Exception : Throwable Exceptions are recoverable errors and must be checked. This is means the exceptions must be explicitly 
thrown to the calling method or caught using a try/catch block.
